      "rationale": "All five COU operating points are covered by validation experiments. The FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry was used throughout. Fluid properties match clinical CPB conditions. The validation campaign is judged relevant to the nominal COU operating envelope. Hardware fault modes arising from prolonged in vivo deployment — bearing wear altering impeller clearance, flow-sensor drift shifting the actual operating point, or electrical transients perturbing motor speed — are outside the scope of the validation activities and are not represented in the model inputs or test conditions."
